  "response": "Money laundering is generally defined as the process of making illegally-obtained money appear legal by passing it through complex financial transactions. Typical elements include:\n\n1. Placement - Introducing illegal funds into the financial system\n2. Layering - Disguising the source through multiple transactions\n3. Integration - Reintroducing the \"cleaned\" money into legitimate economic activities\n\nSpecific legal definitions vary by jurisdiction, but most countries criminalize intentional concealment of funds derived from criminal activities.",
